cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about channel pruning for deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common technique in computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of data-driven ranking criteria, which falls under the umbrella of machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper involves optimizing the computational efficiency of the pruning procedure, which could fall under the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
